# ModalDialog

A IDS modal dialog draws attention to important information by preventing the user from interacting with the main application workflow using a mouse, keyboard, touch, or screen reader, until an action is taken or the dialog is dismissed. An example includes asking the user to save a document before exiting a screen, or asking them for confirmation before deleting something.

IDS Modal dialogs come in three widths: small (384px), medium (576px) and large (752px). The height is flexible and is determined by content. The max-height is 680px.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/modal-dialog
```

```tsx
import { ModalDialog } from '@ids-ts/modal-dialog';
```

## Props

### Modal

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `ReactNode` | Yes | Modal content (ModalHeader, ModalContent, ModalActions). |
| `automationId` | `string` | No | Test automation identifier. |

### ModalTitle

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `title` | `string` | Yes | The modal dialog title text. |

### ModalContent

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `ReactNode` | Yes | Content rendered inside the modal body. |
| `overflow` | `boolean` | No | Enables scrolling when content overflows. |
| `maxHeight` | `string` | No | CSS max-height value (e.g., `'50vh'`). |

### Sub-components

- `ModalHeader` — Header area containing ModalTitle
- `ModalActions` — Footer area for action buttons

